caption: Takis is the best place for breakfast and lunch. I eat there a lot. Love the owner and his wife. They are good people.
The Italian sub combo was incredible!! Highly recommend! Their waitress Eve was lovely! My friend ordered the chicken picatta and it was very tasty!!
I ordered Open chicken through Grubhub and everything was delicious 🤤 not only were the fries still hot but the chicken tender and flavorful. 👌🏽I will order there again.

First of all, their home made tzatziki is the best!!!! I’ve been to many local Greek places, and the one thing that gets me is when the tzatziki is not good, whether the flavor is too muted or the texture is like they tried to make it go further with water; not so at Takis! Their tzatziki is delicious and adds the perfect compliment to a wrap or souvlaki.Their chicken is super tender and flavorful. The chef makes these amazing soups (one is fish soup, bc I don’t remember the name, with pieces of tender white fish) lentil, chicken lemon rice, and plenty of diner usuals as well are in the rotation. Also, since they are located directly on Court St., they offer the fastest takeout, from an actual Resturant- but I would even dare to say I’ve waited longer in a drive through of actual ‘fast food’ places. Their breakfast is great, the potatoes are wonderful and did I mention they’re so so so budget friendly? If you’re leaving the office on a half hr lunch you can go every day and it won’t break the back and your taste buds will thank you! So no matter what you get, don’t forget to add your Tzatziki!!
Everything is homemade! The owners take great pride in knowing their customers!!!

I usually like this place (their burgers are good, but their pancakes leave a lot to be desired), but my last experience here was unpleasant. I had a lunch date and while she looked for a parking space, I ordered a beef quesadilla and she ordered a soup. Although she came in a few minutes later, she received her food first. I thought, no problem, they probably had soup ready to go. So after about 20 minutes of waiting, I flagged down my waitress after she kept ignoring me and asked what was going on...only for her to tell me they had no more beef. So I wasted my lunch hour because they couldn't be bothered to admit the truth and so I just ordered the soup, ate the crackers and threw the wrappers in my untouched soup to show my displeasure. I have yet to come back.

Delicious Food Nice Atmosphere I had the Steak Quesadilla which was very delicious, had to take half of it home. Also grabbed a piece of Baklava to go huge piece for $3.25 and hit the sweet tooth so delectable.  Will definitely be back.  Today, Thursday, November 9, 2017 stopped in on a very cold day for a cup of Chili and sandwich.  The Chili was delicious.  I decided on a regular Grilled Cheese Sandwich, it was blah two thin slices of packaged (you know Kraft or Borden Singles kind) Yellow American Cheese warmed between two thick slices of white Texas Toast bread, too much bread not enough Cheese, although I do not think more single slices of cheese could have improved it. They use Margarine instead of Butter.  The last couple times I've been to Taki's I've been disappointed, they are using bagged salads now instead of fresh, margarine not butter, and single wrapped Cheese over Deli cheese.  What's going on Taking??  But at least the Chili was Awesome it warmed my body.  And their Baklava is always a real treat, I grabbed that to go.

Was suggested that Taki's Restaurant serves great breakfast, so got there and ordered eggs with rear cooked steak. Since I own restaurant on my own I will try not to be harsh on my review. Omelette was cooked exactly the way I asked. Steak had little weird taste, feels like it was either marinated and stayed for couple days or already was close to expiring date. Waitress was amazing and inside of restaurant was clean. Loved pictures on the wall. Have to admit, bathroom looked dirty, maybe because of the color it was painted. Ordered some steak to go. More likely it's roast beef and really salty one. Steak tastes better if you toast it with bread, not separate... Sorry to say that, but, Subway does better job on steak sandwiches than you... Hopefully, you guys have market for your steak sandwich. Prices are reasonable. Problem with parking.

The service at Taki's was phenomenal, and the food was excellent. The workers were patient and friendly when I was ordering. Taki's is rightfully one of the best restaurants in Western New York. When I ordered the club sandwich, my favorite, it always comes to my table in under 10 minutes. Centrally located, it is a perfect place to come on my lunch break. The restaurant is always clean, and has maintained this for as long as I can remember coming here. The owner, Taki, is such a memorable character. He is the type of person that has the personality of likability. This likability carries on through each of his workers, who make you feel comfortable when dining with them. For anyone who enjoys Greek-American food in a classic diner style, this is for you.
